The paper deals with the analysis of a Markov chain algorithm for sampling from the Gibbs distribution of the ferromagnetic Ising model on a graph. This falls under the broad area of probability and statistics in computer science. The paper also uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.PR (Probability), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
